---
title: 2026-05010 讲章
---
## 使徒行传 17:22-31 | Acts 17:22-31

保罗站在亚略巴古当中，说：“众位雅典人哪，我看你们凡事很敬畏鬼神。我游行的时候，观看你们所敬拜的，遇见一座坛，上面写着‘未识之神’。你们所不认识而敬拜的，我现在告诉你们。”
Paul then stood up in the meeting of the Areopagus and said: “People of Athens! I see that in every way you are very religious. For as I walked around and looked carefully at your objects of worship, I even found an altar with this inscription: TO AN UNKNOWN GOD. So you are ignorant of the very thing you worship—and this is what I am going to proclaim to you.”  

“创造宇宙和其中万物的神，既是天地的主，就不住人手所造的殿，也不用人手服事，好像缺少什么；自己倒将生命、气息、万物，赐给万人。他从一本造出万族的人，住在全地上，并且预先定准他们的年限和所住的疆界。”
“The God who made the world and everything in it is the Lord of heaven and earth and does not live in temples built by human hands. And he is not served by human hands, as if he needed anything. Rather, he himself gives everyone life and breath and everything else. From one man he made all the nations, that they should inhabit the whole earth; and he marked out their appointed times in history and the boundaries of their lands.”

“要叫他们寻求神，或者可以揣摩而得，其实他离我们各人不远；我们生活、动作、存留，都在乎他。就如你们作诗的，有人说：‘我们也是他所生的。’”
“God did this so that they would seek him and perhaps reach out for him and find him, though he is not far from any one of us. ‘For in him we live and move and have our being.’ As some of your own poets have said, ‘We are his offspring.’”

“我们既是神所生的，就不当以为神的神性像金、银、石，列在人的手艺、心思所雕刻的。世人蒙昧无知的时候，神并不监察，如今却吩咐各处的人都要悔改。因为他已经定了日子，要借着他所设立的人按公义审判天下，并且叫他从死里复活，给万人作可信的凭据。”
“Therefore since we are God’s offspring, we should not think that the divine being is like gold or silver or stone—an image made by human design and skill. In the past God overlooked such ignorance, but now he commands all people everywhere to repent. For he has set a day when he will judge the world with justice by the man he has appointed. He has given proof of this to everyone by raising him from the dead.”
母亲节讲道 | Mother’s Day Message

祝愿坐在这里的母亲们，以及在其他地方的所有母亲们，母亲节快乐。我们怀念并致敬那些已经回到主那里的母亲，她们因各种原因在肉身上离开了我们。我向所有的母亲、所有的女性、所有的女性同胞致敬，她们不知疲倦地照顾家庭成员，贡献社会，在教会中侍奉基督，特别是在圣大卫·穆拉宾（St David’s Moorabbin）教会。
Happy Mother’s Day to all the mothers sitting here and the mothers out there somewhere, we remember and acknowledge those mothers who had gone to the Lord, who are not with us physically for a lot of reasons. I pay tributes to all mothers, all women, all females who work so tirelessly to look after their family members, to contribute in the society, to serve Christ in churches, especially at St David’s Moorabbin.

我想请大家玩一个小测验：哪三个字能解决爸爸的所有问题？
答案是：“找你妈”（Ask your mother）。
为什么母亲节那天家里那么整洁？
“因为妈妈周六花了一整天在打扫。”
为什么我们的教会运行得如此顺畅有序？
“因为我们有许多勤劳且忠心的姊妹们，在教会建筑的各个角落没日没夜地忙碌着。”
May I have a little quiz for you all: What three words solve Dad’s every problem? The three words are: ‘Ask your mother’. Why was the house so neat on Mother’s Day? ‘Because Mom spent all day Saturday cleaning it." And why our church are running so smoothly and orderly? ‘Because we have many hard working and faithful ladies working around the clock around the church building.’

是的，我们确实需要为妇女联谊会（Ladies Guild）、母佑会（Mothers’ Union）、女性神职人员、女主教和女大主教感谢神。有了敬虔的男女同工，任何教会都会稳步前进，为基督结出美果，并在成长中造福众人。
Yes, we do need to thank God for the Ladies Guild, for the Mothers’ Union, for women clergy, women bishops and archbishops. With godly women and men, any church will advance well, any church may bear good fruit for Christ, any church will grow to bring benefits to many.

无论得时不得时，务要准备好传道并见证基督。自保罗归主以来，他将自己变成了一名传教士，一个只为基督而活的人，他通过服事所有的罪人来服事基督。
In season and out of season, be prepared to preach and witness Christ. Since his conversion, Paul has turned himself into a missionary, into someone who live only for Christ and he served Christ by serving all the sinners.

在使徒行传第17章中，我们看到保罗在帖撒罗尼迦、庇哩亚，接着在雅典的职事。保罗马不停蹄地从一地奔向另一地，传扬基督和他钉十字架的信息。当他到达雅典——那座当时世界上最辉煌、最重要的历史名城时，保罗发现那里偶像崇拜的规模之大，令他感到震惊、压抑且沉重。他看到到处都有人拜金、银或石头做的偶像和雕像。
In Acts chapter 17, we see Paul’s ministry in Thessalonica, then in Berea, then in Athens. Paul travelled non-stop, from a place to another, to proclaim Christ and him crucified. When he arrived Athens, the famous and historic city, one of the most glorious and important cities in the world at that era, Paul discovered and was startled, overwhelmed and depressed by the magnitude of the idolatry, he saw people worshipped idols / statues made of gold or silver or stone everywhere.

保罗看到整个雅典城都陷入了偶像崇拜之中（kateidolos），整座城市被偶像占据或淹没。保罗看到了雅典之美，那是希腊雕刻家和建筑师所能提供的最高杰作；但所有这些美并没有尊崇上帝为宇宙唯一的真神，没有尊崇上帝为万物的源头和本原，而唯有他赐予生命与福分。
Paul saw that the whole city of Athens was given over to idols (kateidolos), the whole city was under idols or swamped by idols. Paul saw the beauty of Athens, having the best that Greek sculptors and architects could offer; but all that beauty did not honor God as the only God of the universe, did not honor God as the origin and the original, who alone grant life and blessings in life.

雅典人敬拜各种神灵，他们敬拜众多的神，甚至敬拜“未识之神”，他们不想漏掉任何神，不想忽略任何神……因此，保罗在心中呐喊：雅典的人民啊，请敬拜基督，给他一个机会！是的，他由于你们也是陌生的，但请寻求他，就必寻见。敬拜他，他必赐予你们赦免与救恩。
People in Athens worshipped any gods, they worshipped many and multiple gods, they even worshipped the unknown god, they didn’t want to leave out any gods, they didn’t want to neglect any gods … thus Paul was crying in his heart… people in Athens: worship Christ, give him a chance, yes he is unknown to you too, please seek him and he will be found. Worship him and he will grant you forgiveness and salvation.

基督教的神从一本造出万族。保罗告诉他们，我们都是通过挪亚传承自亚当的后代，有一位神创造了我们众人，我们也对他负有责任。既然神创造了我们众人，我们就应当寻求主……而且他离我们各人不远。
The Christian God has made from one blood every nation of men and women. Paul told them we are all descended from Adam through Noah, and that there is one God who created us all and to whom we all are obligated. Since God created us all, we should seek the Lord… and He is not far from each one of us.

将上帝视为“大自然母亲”或“地球母亲”是恰当且合适的，这强调了一种哺育、创造和持续存在的神圣同在感，通常凸显了人类与那位掌管自然者的相互联系。我们应当保护地球，尊重自然。我们应当承认并敬拜那位创造天地的，而不是那些人手所造、出于人类构思和努力的事物。我们应当孝敬我们的母亲，她们赋予我们生命，喂养并哺育我们成长为独立的人。
It is right and appropriate to view God as the Mother Nature, or the Mother Earth, emphasizes a nurturing, creative, and sustaining divine presence, often highlighting humanity's interconnectedness with the One who holds and controls the nature. We should preserve the earth, respect the nature. We should acknowledge and worship the One who creates the Heaven and Earth, not the ones which were man made, created by human efforts and human ideas. We should honor our mothers, who give births to us, who feed us and nurture us to grow up as an independent human being.

保罗说：我们既是神所生的，就不当以为神的神性像金、银、石。我们是后代，是从父母、祖父母及历代祖先传承下来的。我们不是来自大爆炸理论，不是来自太空的爆炸或空间的扩张。我们来自生命的源头，我们应当尊重并尊崇这个源头……因此我们要孝敬父母，因此我们要尊崇圣灵，那被吹入人体内的灵，圣灵降临使我们成为真正的基督徒，成为建立基督真实教会的忠实门徒。
Paul says: Therefore since we are the offspring of God, we ought not to think that the Divine Nature is like gold or silver or stone. We are the offspring, we are the descendants from our parents, grandparents and great great great parents. We don’t come from any big bang theory, we don’t come from any explosion in space, or any expansion of space. We come from an origin of life and we should respect and honor such origin… thus we honor our father and mother, thus we honor the Holy Spirit who was breathed into the human body and the Holy Spirit descend to make us authentic Christians, genuine disciples who form and build the real Church of Christ.

圣灵被理解为教会和信徒的母亲，因为她在赐予新的属灵生命、哺育和安慰中扮演着重要角色。圣灵在五旬节“感孕”并诞生了教会，作为信徒重生的媒介，这与母亲在肉身出生中的角色相呼应。圣灵用上帝的真理喂养我们，用上帝的爱哺育我们，因此，圣灵是圣徒的母亲。所以今天我们不仅是在向我们的母亲致敬，我们是在向那位创造我们母亲、掌管大自然、赐给我们圣灵的神致敬。
The Holy Spirit is understood as the Mother of the Church and believers through her role in giving new spiritual life, nurturing, and comforting. The Holy Spirit "conceived" and gave birth to the Church at Pentecost, acting as the agent of rebirth for believers, paralleling the role of a mother in physical birth. The Holy Spirit feeds us with the truth of God, nurtures us with the love of God, the Holy Spirit is therefore the Mother of the holy saints and so today we honor our mothers but not just our mothers. We honor the God who creates our mothers, who holds the nature, who sends us the Holy Spirit.

“世人蒙昧无知的时候，神并不监察，如今却吩咐各处的人都要悔改。”请承认我们的无知，是的，我们过去不了解；是的，我们因拥有各种形式的偶像而冒犯了神；是的，我们没有将神放在首位。我们做错了，现在应当拨乱反正。我们应当悔改，回转，祈求上帝的宽恕并祈求祂的指引。
In the past God overlooked such ignorance, but now he commands all people everywhere to repent. Please admit that we are ignorant, yes we didn’t know, yes we have offended God by having idols in many shapes and forms, yes we have not been putting God first as our number one preference. We did it wrong and now we should do it right. We should repent, turn around, ask God to forgive and ask God to direct.

请千万不要叫圣灵担忧，请千万不要不尊重或污染大自然，请千万不要对你的母亲怀恨在心，无论她曾是多么不完美或如何伤害过你。请千万不要低估上帝对任何人的爱。上帝命定母亲作为祂的代理人来保护和抚养所有的婴儿。我们尊重母职，我们追求成为一个好母亲、敬虔的母亲、舍己且忍耐的母亲，无论我们年纪多大，无论我们的子孙多大。
Please never grieve the Holy Spirit, please never disrespect and contaminate the nature, please never hold grudges against your mother, no matter how imperfect or hurtful she has been. Please never underestimate God’s love for any human being. God has ordained mothers to be his agents to protect and raise up all babies. We respect motherhood and we pursue to be a good mother, to be a godly mother, to be a sacrificial and suffering mother, no matter how old we are, no matter how old our children and grandchildren are.

我们因母亲而感谢神，因神对母亲的扶持与保护而感谢神，因神对所有好母亲的安慰与奖赏而感谢神。母亲的爱源自上帝。母爱是上帝赋予人类的本能之一，我们也明白，上帝的爱永远高于母爱。
We thank God for mothers, we thank God for sustaining and protecting mothers, we thank God for comforting and rewarding all the good mothers. A mother’s love is from God. A mother’s love is one of the human instincts from God, and we understand God’s love is always above a mother’s love.

“……我多次愿意聚集你的儿女，好像母鸡把小鸡聚集在翅膀底下……”（马太福音 23:37 / 路加福音 13:34）
"...how often I have longed to gather your children together, as a hen gathers her chicks under her wings..." (Matthew 23:37 / Luke 13:34)

“母亲怎样安慰儿子，我就照样安慰你们……”（以赛亚书 66:13）
"As a mother comforts her child, so will I comfort you…" (Isaiah 66:13)

“妇人焉能忘记她吃奶的婴孩，不怜恤她所生的儿子？即或有忘记的，我却不忘记你。”（以赛亚书 49:15）
"Can a mother forget the baby at her breast and have no compassion on the child she has borne? Though she may forget, I will not forget you!" (Isaiah 49:15)

神爱世人，祂绝不会忘记我们。让我们向祂献上感谢，永远铭记祂的恩慈。因基督的缘故。阿们。
For God so loved the world, he would never forget us. Let us give him thanks and remember his goodness always. For Christ’s sake. Amen.
